Subject: RE: [T2] Tank Crud - Alternatives?

What would be the hazards of doing this with something
stronger, say Amonia?  I'm no chemist or chemical
engineer, but I've had the crud problems in the past
and currently have it on another vehicle.  Thanks...KR


> Josh, 
> 	Here's what I did when tank crud gave me a problem
> in our 71.
> 1.  First I drained the gas tank.
> 2.  Then I disconnected the fuel line and screwed
> the strainer out of the
> bottom of the tank.  I believe your 72 has the same
> set up.
> 3.  Using a couple of buckets I poured a gallon of
> alcohol into the tank and
> then let it drain out of the strainer hole into a
> second bucket.  I then
> poured it back into the first bucket through a piece
> of cloth to remove the
> crud from the alcohol.
> 4.  Repeat step 3 until no more crud comes out of
> the strainer hole.  Set
> the bucket aside and let the alcohol evaporate.

> http://www.type2.com/donate.html
